> 
> Linus,
> 
> When we were putting SMP on NetWare, we discovered that using the IOAPIC
> hardware for UP systems was almost 4% faster than the 8259-PIC for LAN
> drivers (since it has a dedicated ICC bus to pass interrupt messages to
> a local APIC).  Something to consider....
> 
The problem is that most UP mobos don't *have* IOAPIC's... Linux will
use them if they're there (most commonly on SMP mobos with only one
slot populated, or on mobos which have UP and SMP versions.)
	-hpa
